=begin pod
=TITLE Gnome::Gtk4::FontChooserWidget
=head1 Description

The B<Gnome::Gtk4::FontChooserWidget> widget lets the user select a font.

It is used in the L<Gnome::Gtk4::FontChooserDialog|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/FontChooserDialog> widget to provide a
dialog for selecting fonts.

To set the font which is initially selected, use
L<.set-font() in class FontChooser|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/FontChooser#set-font> or L<.set-font-desc() in class FontChooser|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/FontChooser#set-font-desc>.

To get the selected font use L<.get-font() in class FontChooser|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/FontChooser#get-font> or
L<.get-font-desc() in class FontChooser|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/FontChooser#get-font-desc>.

To change the text which is shown in the preview area, use
L<.set-preview-text() in class FontChooser|/content-docs/api2/reference/Gtk4/FontChooser#set-preview-text>.

=head2 CSS nodes

B<Gnome::Gtk4::FontChooserWidget> has a single CSS node with name fontchooser.

